            What is <em><b><mark>Variables?</em></b></mark>
            In order for the system to do its job, the data needs to be store somewhere.
            That is when the variables came in. The data can be store in variables.<br>
            <br>First, you need to declare a variable. You can use <em><b> var, let, or const. </em></b>
            Most developers will use either <em><b>let</em></b> or <em><b>const</b></em> to declare a variable.
            <em><b>const</em></b> is the same as <em><b>let</em></b> variable except, it cannot be reassigned.<br>
            <br>Let's take a look at some examples to how to declare a variables.<br>
            <pre>let >> variable keyword<br>grocery>> variable name<br>avocado>> variable value<br>let grocery = avocado;</pre>
